ian restaurants, they start their menu with appetizers…one definitely worth\r\ntrying is their arancini:\r\n\r\n','RESTAURANT REVIEW: AMICO BIO, LONDON’S  PREMIER ITALIAN VEGETARIAN RESTAURANT','','inherit','open','open','','179-revision-v1','','','2014-04-10 18:49:56','2014-04-10 18:49:56','',179,'http://localhost/london-food/179-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `jc_posts` VALUES (181,1,'2014-04-10 18:52:01','2014-04-10 18:52:01','<a href=\"http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_4459.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-282\" alt=\"img_4459\" src=\"http://londonfoodlovers.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/img_4459-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\r\n\r\nI’ve only been here for less than a week, yet the vibe in this city is pretty clear: “London is on the move”.In one week, I’ve seen sun, rain, wind, currently a tube strike, and yet nothing stops these people. Yesterday I had to get into the city center and ended up walking most of the way since there was so much traffic. Initially I was a bit worried about getting lost, but it was a lot easier than I thought and it was lovely to see all of the people going about their days, despite the rain and crowds. Pubs were filled, cafés were busy, and restaurants were running as normal.\r\n\r\nIn Rome, I remember not wanting to leave the house if we had the slightest bit of rain… And people would panic when the roads were wet, getting into silly accidents and slowing traffic to a halt. In London? You’ve got a strike? You’ve got an enormous traffic jam? What do you do!? Rain or no rain..you WALK! You ‘ve got to give it to Londoners-nothing gets in their way\r\n\r\nWe will answer all of your questions by phone or email once we receive the completed Private Tour Request Form.','RAIN, WIND, TRANSPORTATION STRIKES… NOTHING STOPS LONDONERS FROM  ENJOYING THEMSELVES.','I’ve only been here for less than a week, yet the vibe in this city is pretty clear','publish','open','open','','rain-wind-transportation-strikes-nothing-stops-londoners-from-enjoying-themselves','','','2014-04-21 01:43:04','2014-04-21 01:43:04','',0,'http://localhost/london-food/?p=181',0,'post','',0);
